 - Candidate Document: Definition of GNP, or Gross National Product, is an economic measure representing the total value of all goods and services produced by the citizens of a country, including those working or investing abroad. GNP includes income earned by the country’s residents from their investments and work overseas, making it a more comprehensive indicator of economic health than GDP. Calculated by adding net income from abroad to GDP, GNP offers insights into a country's overall economic performance and wealth. Economists use GNP data for detailed analysis and policy-making, reflecting the global contributions of a country's residents. While related to GDP, GNP provides a broader view of a country's economic well-being.

Regular vocal exercises and warm-ups can strengthen your vocal cords and reduce the risk of hoarseness. Proper posture and breathing techniques support vocal health. Consistent care and attention to these practices can significantly help in preventing hoarseness. Maintaining a humid environment and using a humidifier can keep the vocal cords moist. Avoiding smoking and secondhand smoke is crucial as they can cause significant irritation. By adhering to these recommendations, you can effectively prevent hoarseness and maintain a healthy, clear voice. Regular check-ups with a speech therapist or ENT specialist can provide personalized advice.
